text.section:
An issuer may issue bonds for the purpose of providing funds with which:
To fund floating indebtedness;
To fund the cost of providing a public service if the governing body determines that an emergency exists and the public health or safety so requires;
To fund unfunded liabilities;
To establish a reserve for past or future liabilities or casualties; or
To pay one (1) or more final judgments rendered against the issuer, including settlements of claims approved by a court.
